{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HVdBqDPgUb7qDJgY3owDPr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→#!/usr/bin/env bash\n     2→# run-e2e-local.sh — Single-entrypoint for local E2E tests.\n     3→# Runs: bootstrap → Playwright tests → teardown (always).\n     4→set -euo pipefail\n     5→\n     6→SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"${BASH_SOURCE[0]}\")\" && pwd)\"\n     7→APP_DIR=\"$(cd \"$SCRIPT_DIR/..\" && pwd)\"\n     8→\n     9→# --- Bootstrap ---\n    10→echo \"==> Starting localnet validator…\"\n    11→if ! bash \"$SCRIPT_DIR/localnet-bootstrap.sh\"; then\n    12→  echo \"❌ Localnet bootstrap failed\"\n    13→  bash \"$SCRIPT_DIR/localnet-teardown.sh\" 2>/dev/null || true\n    14→  exit 1\n    15→fi\n    16→\n    17→# --- Run tests (capture exit code, always teardown after) ---\n    18→echo \"==> Running local E2E tests…\"\n    19→TEST_EXIT=0\n    20→(cd \"$APP_DIR\" && npx playwright test --config playwright.local.config.ts) || TEST_EXIT=$?\n    21→\n    22→# --- Teardown (always) ---\n    23→echo \"==> Stopping localnet validator…\"\n    24→bash \"$SCRIPT_DIR/localnet-teardown.sh\" || true\n    25→\n    26→# --- Report ---\n    27→if [ \"$TEST_EXIT\" -eq 0 ]; then\n    28→  echo \"✅ Local E2E tests passed\"\n    29→else\n    30→  echo \"❌ Local E2E tests failed (exit $TEST_EXIT)\"\n    31→fi\n    32→\n    33→exit \"$TEST_EXIT\"\n    34→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011NmLDGpD21DxpEiJBkRt9S","session_id":"fa72ea81-f347-48b5-9c89-c72eb0bf80d0","uuid":"9f577398-756e-4f22-a364-d3b6f9555470"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011NmLDGpD21DxpEiJBkRt9S","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile the findings into a comprehensive exploration report.\n\n## E2E Test Infrastructure Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the platform E2E test infrastructure. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n### 1. Playwright Configurations (Three Modes)\n\n**Local E2E Config** (`playwright.local.config.ts`):\n- Tests against **local `solana-test-validator`** with real wallet mode\n- Single worker, no parallelization (`fullyParallel: false`)\n- Runs on `http://localhost:3002` with 60-second timeout\n- Enables `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true` for test wallet injection\n- Disables mock mode (`VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"`)\n- RPC points to local validator (`http://127.0.0.1:8899`)\n- Retains traces on failure for debugging\n- Tests match `local/**/*.spec.ts`\n\n**Visual Regression Config** (`playwright.config.ts`):\n- Tests against mock mode (`VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"true\"`)\n- Fully parallel execution (`fullyParallel: true`)\n- Runs on `http://localhost:3000` (standard Vite port)\n- Visual snapshot threshold: `maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.015` (1.5%)\n- Tests match `visual/**/*.spec.ts`\n- Used for visual consistency testing without external dependencies\n\n**Real Wallet Config** (`playwright.real.config.ts`):\n- Tests against **devnet** with real wallet mode\n- Fully parallel execution\n- Runs on `http://localhost:3001`\n- RPC points to Solana devnet (`https://api.devnet.solana.com`)\n- Tests match `real/**/*.spec.ts`\n\n### 2. Environment Validation (`env.ts`)\n\nThe devnet helper provides a robust **DevnetConfig** contract that:\n- **Validates all required env vars** before tests run (fails fast):\n  - `VITE_RPC_URL` (HTTP/HTTPS URL validation)\n  - `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` (base58 public key validation)\n  - `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` (base58 public key validation)\n  - `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` (optional, defaults to \"devnet\")\n- **Hardcoded Orao VRF program ID** (`VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y`)\n- **Two verification phases**:\n  1. RPC health check via `getLatestBlockhash()`\n  2. Program deployment verification (checks if programs are executable at specified addresses)\n  3. Orao VRF initialization check (verifies network state PDA exists)\n\n### 3. Dual-Player Fixtures (`fixtures.ts`)\n\nCustom Playwright fixture providing:\n- **Two isolated browser contexts** (playerA/playerB) with no cross-contamination\n- **Deterministic keypair injection** via `addInitScript` — seeds stored at `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`\n- **Fixtures exported**:\n  - `playerAContext` / `playerBContext` — isolated browser contexts\n  - `playerAPage` / `playerBPage` — ready-to-use pages\n  - `playerAKeypair` / `playerBKeypair` — keypair objects\n  - `connection` — shared RPC connection to local validator\n- Uses custom test runner extending `@playwright/test` base\n\n### 4. Wallet Helpers (`wallets.ts`)\n\nDeterministic wallet setup for reproducible tests:\n- **Two fixed keypairs** from seed bytes:\n  - `PLAYER_A` from seed `0xaaaa...aaaa` (32 bytes of 0xaa)\n  - `PLAYER_B` from seed `0xbbbb...bbbb` (32 bytes of 0xbb)\n- **Default airdrop**: 10 SOL per wallet\n- **Key function `fundTestWallets()`**:\n  - Airdrops SOL to both players\n  - Confirms transactions before proceeding\n  - Validates minimum balance reached\n  - Returns keypairs + connection for test use\n- Local RPC URL hardcoded as `http://127.0.0.1:8899`\n\n### 5. Bootstrap & Teardown Scripts\n\n**localnet-bootstrap.sh**:\n- Starts fresh `solana-test-validator` with programs pre-deployed at genesis\n- **Preflight checks**:\n  - Verifies `.so` files exist (coinflip + platform)\n  - Verifies keypair files exist\n  - Checks for io_uring availability (Solana 3.x requirement)\n- **Kills any existing validator** on port 8899\n- **Cleans ledger** for fresh state each run\n- **Preloads Orao VRF mock accounts** from `scripts/localnet-accounts/`:\n  - Network state PDA\n  - Random player accounts\n  - Treasury account\n- **Polls RPC health** with 30-second timeout\n- Writes validator PID to `.localnet.pid` for teardown tracking\n- Logs to `.localnet-validator.log`\n\n**localnet-teardown.sh**:\n- Gracefully stops validator via PID file (reads `.localnet.pid`)\n- **Optional `--keep-logs` flag** to preserve validator logs\n- Kills any stray processes on port 8899\n- Cleans up `.localnet-ledger` directory\n- Safe to call multiple times (idempotent)\n\n**run-e2e-local.sh** (Single Entrypoint):\n- Orchestrates: bootstrap → tests → teardown\n- **Always runs teardown** (via `exit $TEST_EXIT`) even if tests fail\n- Captures test exit code and re-reports it\n- Prevents validator from lingering after test failures\n\n### 6. NPM Scripts in `package.json`\n\n| Script | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `test:visual` | Run visual regression tests (`playwright test`) |\n| `test:visual:update` | Update visual snapshots |\n| `test:real` | Run devnet E2E tests (`--config playwright.real.config.ts`) |\n| `test:e2e:local` | Run local E2E tests (`--config playwright.local.config.ts`) |\n| `test:e2e` | Full local E2E (bootstrap → tests → teardown) |\n\n### 7. Test Scripts Location\n\nAll scripts in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/`:\n- `localnet-bootstrap.sh`\n- `localnet-teardown.sh`\n- `run-e2e-local.sh`\n\n### Architecture Summary\n\n```\nE2E Infrastructure\n├── Visual Tests (Mock Mode)\n│   └── playwright.config.ts → localhost:3000 (pnpm dev)\n├── Local E2E Tests (Real Wallet + Test Validator)\n│   ├── playwright.local.config.ts → localhost:3002\n│   ├── e2e/local/fixtures.ts (dual-player contexts)\n│   ├── e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts (deterministic funding)\n│   └── scripts/ (bootstrap/teardown orchestration)\n└── Devnet E2E Tests (Real Wallet + Devnet RPC)\n    ├── playwright.real.config.ts → localhost:3001 (devnet RPC)\n    └── e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts (config validation + health checks)\n```\n\n**Key Design Patterns**:\n1. **Config separation** — different Playwright configs for different modes (no conditionals in a single config)\n2. **Environment contract** — devnet validation fails fast before tests run\n3. **Deterministic wallets** — fixed keypair seeds enable reproducible multi-player scenarios\n4. **Browser context isolation** — dual fixtures prevent state leakage between players\n5. **Script orchestration** — bootstrap/teardown always run, with clean ledger per test cycle"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad54224a362454784 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40874\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 26512</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fa72ea81-f347-48b5-9c89-c72eb0bf80d0","uuid":"64389610-5bb1-4bce-8dc6-6287b1e1c1cb","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the E2E test infrastructure for the platform app. I need to understand:\n\n1. The existing local E2E Playwright config at `apps/platform/playwright.local.config.ts` - read the full file\n2. The existing visual regression config at `apps/platform/playwright.config.ts` - read the full file\n3. The existing real-mode config at `apps/platform/playwright.real.config.ts` - read the full file (if exists)\n4. The devnet env helper at `apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts` - read the full file\n5. The local fixtures at `apps/platform/e2e/local/fixtures.ts` - read the full file\n6. The local wallets helper at `apps/platform/e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts` - read the full file\n7. All scripts in `apps/platform/scripts/` - list them\n8. The `apps/platform/package.json` - read the scripts section\n\nAll paths are relative to `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/`. Read all files fully.","agentId":"ad54224a362454784","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile the findings into a comprehensive exploration report.\n\n## E2E Test Infrastructure Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the platform E2E test infrastructure. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n### 1. Playwright Configurations (Three Modes)\n\n**Local E2E Config** (`playwright.local.config.ts`):\n- Tests against **local `solana-test-validator`** with real wallet mode\n- Single worker, no parallelization (`fullyParallel: false`)\n- Runs on `http://localhost:3002` with 60-second timeout\n- Enables `VITE_TEST_WALLET=true` for test wallet injection\n- Disables mock mode (`VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"`)\n- RPC points to local validator (`http://127.0.0.1:8899`)\n- Retains traces on failure for debugging\n- Tests match `local/**/*.spec.ts`\n\n**Visual Regression Config** (`playwright.config.ts`):\n- Tests against mock mode (`VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"true\"`)\n- Fully parallel execution (`fullyParallel: true`)\n- Runs on `http://localhost:3000` (standard Vite port)\n- Visual snapshot threshold: `maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.015` (1.5%)\n- Tests match `visual/**/*.spec.ts`\n- Used for visual consistency testing without external dependencies\n\n**Real Wallet Config** (`playwright.real.config.ts`):\n- Tests against **devnet** with real wallet mode\n- Fully parallel execution\n- Runs on `http://localhost:3001`\n- RPC points to Solana devnet (`https://api.devnet.solana.com`)\n- Tests match `real/**/*.spec.ts`\n\n### 2. Environment Validation (`env.ts`)\n\nThe devnet helper provides a robust **DevnetConfig** contract that:\n- **Validates all required env vars** before tests run (fails fast):\n  - `VITE_RPC_URL` (HTTP/HTTPS URL validation)\n  - `VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID` (base58 public key validation)\n  - `VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID` (base58 public key validation)\n  - `VITE_SOLANA_NETWORK` (optional, defaults to \"devnet\")\n- **Hardcoded Orao VRF program ID** (`VRFzZoJdhFWL8rkvu87LpKM3RbcVezpMEc6X5GVDr7y`)\n- **Two verification phases**:\n  1. RPC health check via `getLatestBlockhash()`\n  2. Program deployment verification (checks if programs are executable at specified addresses)\n  3. Orao VRF initialization check (verifies network state PDA exists)\n\n### 3. Dual-Player Fixtures (`fixtures.ts`)\n\nCustom Playwright fixture providing:\n- **Two isolated browser contexts** (playerA/playerB) with no cross-contamination\n- **Deterministic keypair injection** via `addInitScript` — seeds stored at `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`\n- **Fixtures exported**:\n  - `playerAContext` / `playerBContext` — isolated browser contexts\n  - `playerAPage` / `playerBPage` — ready-to-use pages\n  - `playerAKeypair` / `playerBKeypair` — keypair objects\n  - `connection` — shared RPC connection to local validator\n- Uses custom test runner extending `@playwright/test` base\n\n### 4. Wallet Helpers (`wallets.ts`)\n\nDeterministic wallet setup for reproducible tests:\n- **Two fixed keypairs** from seed bytes:\n  - `PLAYER_A` from seed `0xaaaa...aaaa` (32 bytes of 0xaa)\n  - `PLAYER_B` from seed `0xbbbb...bbbb` (32 bytes of 0xbb)\n- **Default airdrop**: 10 SOL per wallet\n- **Key function `fundTestWallets()`**:\n  - Airdrops SOL to both players\n  - Confirms transactions before proceeding\n  - Validates minimum balance reached\n  - Returns keypairs + connection for test use\n- Local RPC URL hardcoded as `http://127.0.0.1:8899`\n\n### 5. Bootstrap & Teardown Scripts\n\n**localnet-bootstrap.sh**:\n- Starts fresh `solana-test-validator` with programs pre-deployed at genesis\n- **Preflight checks**:\n  - Verifies `.so` files exist (coinflip + platform)\n  - Verifies keypair files exist\n  - Checks for io_uring availability (Solana 3.x requirement)\n- **Kills any existing validator** on port 8899\n- **Cleans ledger** for fresh state each run\n- **Preloads Orao VRF mock accounts** from `scripts/localnet-accounts/`:\n  - Network state PDA\n  - Random player accounts\n  - Treasury account\n- **Polls RPC health** with 30-second timeout\n- Writes validator PID to `.localnet.pid` for teardown tracking\n- Logs to `.localnet-validator.log`\n\n**localnet-teardown.sh**:\n- Gracefully stops validator via PID file (reads `.localnet.pid`)\n- **Optional `--keep-logs` flag** to preserve validator logs\n- Kills any stray processes on port 8899\n- Cleans up `.localnet-ledger` directory\n- Safe to call multiple times (idempotent)\n\n**run-e2e-local.sh** (Single Entrypoint):\n- Orchestrates: bootstrap → tests → teardown\n- **Always runs teardown** (via `exit $TEST_EXIT`) even if tests fail\n- Captures test exit code and re-reports it\n- Prevents validator from lingering after test failures\n\n### 6. NPM Scripts in `package.json`\n\n| Script | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `test:visual` | Run visual regression tests (`playwright test`) |\n| `test:visual:update` | Update visual snapshots |\n| `test:real` | Run devnet E2E tests (`--config playwright.real.config.ts`) |\n| `test:e2e:local` | Run local E2E tests (`--config playwright.local.config.ts`) |\n| `test:e2e` | Full local E2E (bootstrap → tests → teardown) |\n\n### 7. Test Scripts Location\n\nAll scripts in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/`:\n- `localnet-bootstrap.sh`\n- `localnet-teardown.sh`\n- `run-e2e-local.sh`\n\n### Architecture Summary\n\n```\nE2E Infrastructure\n├── Visual Tests (Mock Mode)\n│   └── playwright.config.ts → localhost:3000 (pnpm dev)\n├── Local E2E Tests (Real Wallet + Test Validator)\n│   ├── playwright.local.config.ts → localhost:3002\n│   ├── e2e/local/fixtures.ts (dual-player contexts)\n│   ├── e2e/local/helpers/wallets.ts (deterministic funding)\n│   └── scripts/ (bootstrap/teardown orchestration)\n└── Devnet E2E Tests (Real Wallet + Devnet RPC)\n    ├── playwright.real.config.ts → localhost:3001 (devnet RPC)\n    └── e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts (config validation + health checks)\n```\n\n**Key Design Patterns**:\n1. **Config separation** — different Playwright configs for different modes (no conditionals in a single config)\n2. **Environment contract** — devnet validation fails fast before tests run\n3. **Deterministic wallets** — fixed keypair seeds enable reproducible multi-player scenarios\n4. **Browser context isolation** — dual fixtures prevent state leakage between players\n5. **Script orchestration** — bootstrap/teardown always run, with clean ledger per test cycle"}],"totalDurationMs":26512,"totalTokens":40874,"totalToolUseCount":11,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4820,"cache_read_input_tokens":34088,"output_tokens":1959,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4820,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
